The work will be the the sum of the area under the curve for each step in
 the cycle,.
 which in this case will correspond to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
W=\left(T_{h}-T_{c}\right)\left(S_{h}-S_{c}\right),
\]

\end_inset

now for the heat, we need to make use the of the first law, and in this
